HEADWORD: Poss
<hw>Poss</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Push</er>.]</ety> <def>To push; to dash; to throw.</def> <mark>[Obs.
or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A cat . . . <qex>possed</qex> them [the rats] about.</q>
<rj><qau>Piers Plowman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Posse</ent>⟦br⟧
